from fastapi import FastAPI, Depends, status, HTTPException
from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import AsyncSession
from sqlalchemy import select
from typing import List

from .database import init_db, get_db
from .models import User
from .schemas import UserSearchQuery, UserResponse
from .enums import UserRole

app = FastAPI()

@app.on_event("startup")
async def on_startup():
    await init_db()
    # Add some dummy data if the database is empty (for testing)
    async with AsyncSessionLocal() as session:
        if (await session.execute(select(User))).scalar_one_or_none() is None:
            session.add(User(name="Alice Smith", email="alice@example.com", role=UserRole.ADMIN))
            session.add(User(name="Bob Johnson", email="bob@example.com", role=UserRole.EDITOR))
            session.add(User(name="Charlie Brown", email="charlie@example.com", role=UserRole.VIEWER))
            session.add(User(name="David Lee", email="david@example.com", role=UserRole.ADMIN))
            session.add(User(name="Eve White", email="eve@example.com", role=UserRole.VIEWER))
            await session.commit()


@app.get("/search", response_model=List[UserResponse])
async def search_users(
    query_params: UserSearchQuery = Depends(),
    db: AsyncSession = Depends(get_db)
):
    """
    Searches for users based on name and role.
    Supports partial and case-insensitive name matching.
    """
    stmt = select(User)

    if query_params.name:
        # Apply case-insensitive partial match for name
        stmt = stmt.where(User.name.ilike(f"%{query_params.name}%"))
    
    if query_params.role:
        # Apply exact match for role
        stmt = stmt.where(User.role == query_params.role)

    # Apply pagination
    stmt = stmt.offset(query_params.skip).limit(query_params.limit)

    try:
        result = await db.execute(stmt)
        users = result.scalars().all()
        return users
    except Exception as e:
        raise HTTPException(
            status_code=status.HTTP_500_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR,
            detail=f"An error occurred while searching for users: {e}"
        )

# http://localhost:8000/search?name=e&role=viewer
# http://localhost:8000/search?limit=2
# http://localhost:8000/search?skip=1&limit=2
